Work Breakdown Structure (WBS)
Knowing Eye: Web-Based Examination Platform with Behavioral Monitoring

1. Project Initiation & Planning
	1.1 Project Understanding and Scope Definition
		1.1.1 Review project documents, system architecture, and requirements
			1.1.1.1 Analyze the MAIN_DOCUMENT.docx for objectives and scope
			1.1.1.2 Understand the significance of the study for examination integrity
			1.1.1.3 Identify key objectives: centralized platform, exam management, monitoring, computer vision analysis, deep learning integration, behavior scoring, administrative dashboard, and evaluation
		1.1.2 Define system scope, boundaries, and constraints
			1.1.2.1 Limit to web-based desktop/laptop environments with webcams
			1.1.2.2 Exclude mobile applications, external database integration, biometric hardware, and nationwide deployment
			1.1.2.3 Focus on behavioral indicators rather than definitive cheating accusations
			1.1.2.4 Target institutions like LTO, TESDA, and higher education for computer-based examinations
		1.1.3 Identify stakeholders (administrators, examinees, developers)
			1.1.3.1 Define administrator roles: exam creation, monitoring, report review
			1.1.3.2 Define examinee roles: participating in monitored online exams
			1.1.3.3 Define developer roles: system design, implementation, testing
		1.1.4 Define user roles and permissions (admin, examiner, examinee)
			1.1.4.1 Establish role-based access control (RBAC) for security
			1.1.4.2 Assign permissions for exam management, session monitoring, and report access
		1.1.5 Establish system objectives aligned with study goals
			1.1.5.1 Objective 1: Design centralized web-based examination platform
			1.1.5.2 Objective 2: Implement examination management module
			1.1.5.3 Objective 3: Develop monitoring and data management system
			1.1.5.4 Objective 4: Apply computer vision for real-time behavior analysis
			1.1.5.5 Objective 5: Integrate deep learning algorithms (YOLO, CNN, FaceNet/ArcFace)
			1.1.5.6 Objective 6: Develop behavior monitoring and scoring module
			1.1.5.7 Objective 7: Generate administrative dashboard for visualization
			1.1.5.8 Objective 8: Evaluate functionality, usability, and effectiveness
	1.2 Requirements Engineering
		1.2.1 Gather functional requirements (exam, monitoring, reporting)
			1.2.1.1 Define exam creation and configuration requirements
			1.2.1.2 Specify session-guided online exam delivery
			1.2.1.3 Outline webcam capture and video stream handling
			1.2.1.4 Detail facial detection, posture analysis, and behavioral monitoring
			1.2.1.5 Describe anomaly flagging and scoring engine
			1.2.1.6 Specify administrative dashboard and report generation
		1.2.2 Gather non-functional requirements (performance, scalability, usability)
			1.2.2.1 Define performance metrics for real-time processing
			1.2.2.2 Establish scalability for institutional use
			1.2.2.3 Ensure usability for administrators and examinees
			1.2.2.4 Specify security and privacy requirements for video data
		1.2.3 Define system workflows (exam flow, monitoring flow)
			1.2.3.1 Map out examinee exam workflow: login, exam selection, question navigation, submission
			1.2.3.2 Design monitoring workflow: webcam access, frame capture, AI analysis, alert generation
			1.2.3.3 Outline administrator workflow: exam setup, session monitoring, report review
		1.2.4 Create use case diagrams and user stories
			1.2.4.1 Develop use cases for each user role
			1.2.4.2 Write user stories for key features (e.g., "As an admin, I want to create exams")
		1.2.5 Define acceptance criteria for all major features
			1.2.5.1 Set criteria for exam management functionality
			1.2.5.2 Define criteria for monitoring accuracy and real-time performance
			1.2.5.3 Establish criteria for dashboard usability and data visualization
	1.3 Project Planning
		1.3.1 Develop Agile backlog (epics, user stories, tasks)
			1.3.1.1 Create epics for major objectives (platform development, AI integration, etc.)
			1.3.1.2 Break down epics into user stories and tasks
		1.3.2 Define sprint structure and timelines
			1.3.2.1 Plan sprints aligned with capstone project timeline
			1.3.2.2 Allocate time for analysis, design, implementation, testing, evaluation
		1.3.3 Assign roles and responsibilities within the team
			1.3.3.1 Assign backend development tasks
			1.3.3.2 Assign frontend development tasks
			1.3.3.3 Assign AI module development tasks
		1.3.4 Define Definition of Done (DoD) and testing standards
			1.3.4.1 Establish DoD criteria for each task type
			1.3.4.2 Define testing standards for unit, integration, and system tests
		1.3.5 Establish risk management plan
			1.3.5.1 Identify risks: technical challenges in AI integration, privacy concerns
			1.3.5.2 Develop mitigation strategies for identified risks
2. System Architecture Design
	2.1 High-Level Architecture Design
		2.1.1 Define system architecture (modular monolith or layered architecture)
			2.1.1.1 Choose layered architecture for separation of concerns
			2.1.1.2 Design modular structure for scalability
		2.1.2 Identify system components (frontend, backend, AI module, database)
			2.1.2.1 Define frontend component (React + Vite)
			2.1.2.2 Define backend component (Django + REST + Channels)
			2.1.2.3 Define AI module for computer vision processing
			2.1.2.4 Specify database component (SQLite for development, PostgreSQL for production)
		2.1.3 Define communication protocols (REST APIs, WebSocket)
			2.1.3.1 Use REST APIs for CRUD operations
			2.1.3.2 Implement WebSocket for real-time monitoring
		2.1.4 Design system deployment architecture
			2.1.4.1 Plan deployment for web-based environment
			2.1.4.2 Consider cloud hosting options within scope
	2.2 Backend Architecture Design
		2.2.1 Define backend framework structure (Django + Django REST + Channels)
			2.2.1.1 Set up Django project structure
			2.2.1.2 Integrate Django REST Framework for APIs
			2.2.1.3 Configure Channels for WebSocket support
		2.2.2 Design modular feature-based structure
			2.2.2.1 Organize features: authentication, exams, sessions, monitoring, reports
			2.2.2.2 Implement service-repository pattern for data access
		2.2.3 Define service-repository pattern
			2.2.3.1 Create base repository classes for data operations
			2.2.3.2 Develop service layer for business logic
		2.2.4 Design API structure and routing
			2.2.4.1 Define RESTful API endpoints for all features
			2.2.4.2 Implement URL routing and versioning
		2.2.5 Define authentication and authorization strategy
			2.2.5.1 Implement JWT or session-based authentication
			2.2.5.2 Set up role-based permissions
	2.3 Frontend Architecture Design
		2.3.1 Define frontend framework structure (React + Vite)
			2.3.1.1 Initialize React application with Vite
			2.3.1.2 Set up TypeScript for type safety
		2.3.2 Design component hierarchy and routing
			2.3.2.1 Plan component structure for features
			2.3.2.2 Implement routing with React Router
		2.3.3 Define state management approach
			2.3.3.1 Choose state management solution (Context API or Redux)
			2.3.3.2 Design global state for user sessions and monitoring data
		2.3.4 Plan UI/UX layout and navigation structure
			2.3.4.1 Design responsive layouts for desktop/laptop
			2.3.4.2 Plan navigation for admin and examinee interfaces
	2.4 AI & Monitoring Architecture Design
		2.4.1 Define AI pipeline architecture
			2.4.1.1 Design pipeline for frame acquisition to analysis output
			2.4.1.2 Ensure real-time processing capabilities
		2.4.2 Design frame acquisition and preprocessing flow
			2.4.2.1 Implement webcam frame capture
			2.4.2.2 Add preprocessing: normalization, resizing, noise reduction
		2.4.3 Define model integration strategy (YOLO, CNN, FaceNet/ArcFace)
			2.4.3.1 Integrate YOLO for face and posture detection
			2.4.3.2 Implement CNN for feature extraction
			2.4.3.3 Use FaceNet/ArcFace for facial identity verification
		2.4.4 Design real-time processing pipeline
			2.4.4.1 Optimize for low latency in behavioral analysis
			2.4.4.2 Handle frame buffering and sequential processing
		2.4.5 Define output format for behavioral analysis
			2.4.5.1 Structure outputs for anomaly detection and scoring
			2.4.5.2 Format data for backend storage and dashboard visualization
	2.5 Database Design
		2.5.1 Identify entities (users, exams, sessions, logs, alerts)
			2.5.1.1 Define User entity with roles
			2.5.1.2 Define Exam and Question entities
			2.5.1.3 Define Session, Log, and Alert entities
		2.5.2 Define relational schema and normalization
			2.5.2.1 Establish relationships between entities
			2.5.2.2 Normalize to reduce redundancy
		2.5.3 Establish foreign keys and constraints
			2.5.3.1 Implement referential integrity
			2.5.3.2 Add validation constraints
		2.5.4 Design indexing strategy for performance
			2.5.4.1 Index frequently queried fields
			2.5.4.2 Optimize for real-time data access
		2.5.5 Ensure compatibility (SQLite → PostgreSQL migration)
			2.5.5.1 Design schema compatible with both databases
			2.5.5.2 Plan migration scripts for production
